Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] This is a statement by our [Croatian] Foreign 
Minister [Mate] Granic after a brief meeting with [British 
Foreign Secretary] Douglas Hurd: 
  [Begin Granic recording] We talked about the situation in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. We talked about the latest round of talks 
in Geneva. I briefed Mr. Hurd on the results of the Geneva 
conference, especially on the importance of the joint 
declaration on the normalization of interstate relations and the 
settlement of the UN Protected Areas, which we signed with the 
FRY. [end recording] 

